  <!-- ====== HERO ====== -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <p class="hero-eyebrow">Stories, kindness, and a little forest magic</p>
      <h1>Welcome to Norbert&#8217;s Enchanted Forest</h1>
      <p class="hero-tagline">A gentle place to land, listen to stories, and let your imagination wander somewhere kinder. With Norbert as your guide, the forest becomes a place of comfort, courage, and quiet belonging for children and grown-ups alike.</p>
      <div class="hero-cta">
        <a href="enchanted-forest.html" class="btn btn--primary">Enter the Forest</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ====== MEET NORBERT ====== -->
  <section class="section intro texture-overlay">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="intro-grid">
        <div class="intro-image fade-in">
          <img src="images/norbert-forest.jpg" alt="Norbert Barkah sitting in the forest among wildflowers, looking noble and present" style="width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; border-radius: 16px;">
        </div>
        <div class="intro-text fade-in">
          <h2>Meet Norbert</h2>
          <p>Norbert is the heart of this enchanted world. Gentle, watchful, and deeply comforting, he has a way of helping people feel calmer just by being himself. In storytime videos, he listens, settles in, and sometimes snores right in the middle of a tale, and somehow that simple sweetness has become part of the comfort people return for.</p>
          <p>He is real, not imagined, and that is part of what makes him different. Norbert loves children, tiny dogs, cats, and kindhearted people. He has a special gift for helping nervous little ones feel safe, and a quiet protectiveness that reminds me to pay attention when something feels off. In these stories, and in life, he is a steady guide, leading with gentleness, courage, and heart.</p>
          <blockquote style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-style: italic; color: var(--forest-deep); font-size: 1.45rem; margin: 1.5rem 0 1rem; border-left: 3px solid var(--gold-glow); padding-left: 1rem;">"In the forest and in life, I have learned to trust the dog."</blockquote>
          <a href="about.html" class="btn btn--dark-outline" style="margin-top: 1rem;">Meet Norbert</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ====== FEATURED BOOK ====== -->
  <section class="section featured-book">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="book-showcase fade-in">
        <div class="book-cover">
          <img src="images/tug-of-war-lesson-cover.jpg" alt="The Tug of War Lesson book cover - a watercolor illustration of a girl and Norbert sharing a gentle moment by the water, by Susan Higgins">
        </div>
        <div class="book-details">
          <p class="book-genre">Featured Book</p>
          <h2>The Tug of War Lesson</h2>
          <p class="section-subtitle" style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">The first published story in The Norbert Barkah Chronicles</p>
          <p style="font-style: italic; color: var(--gold-glow); font-size: 1.2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">What if the bravest thing is choosing not to pull?</p>
          <p>When Norbert worries he may meet a bully, he learns that real strength does not always mean fighting back. Sometimes it means listening to your heart, letting go of the rope, and making room for something softer to grow.</p>
          <p>As the first published story in The Norbert Barkah Chronicles, this book opens the door to a world of emotional truth, brave choices, kindness, and the quiet light we all carry within.</p>
          <div class="book-actions">
            <a href="books.html" class="btn btn--primary">See the Book</a>
            <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Tug-War-Lesson-Norbert-Barkah/dp/1945567627/" class="btn btn--dark-outline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Where to Buy</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ====== READER QUOTE ====== -->
  <section class="section story-world" style="padding: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem) 0;">
    <div class="container container--narrow text-center">
      <div class="fade-in">
        <div id="homepage-quote">
          <p id="quote-text" style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 2.5vw, 1.7rem); font-style: italic; color: var(--cream); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 1rem;"></p>
          <p id="quote-author" style="color: var(--sage-light); font-size: 1rem;"></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script>
    (function() {
      var reviews = [
        { text: "I am a huge fan of Norbert and his message of kindness on IG so I had to get this book. It was meant to be a gift for my best friend for her preschool classroom but I couldn't part with it once I opened it up. The message and the pictures. It just warmed my heart.", author: "Marisa D., Amazon Verified Purchase" },
        { text: "After a rough day her stories bring me back to a calmer, better world. So looking forward to their next book!", author: "Mike K., Amazon Verified Purchase" },
        { text: "This is a beautifully written story about kindness and forgiveness and lastly letting go. This book shows how letting go leads to better things in life. A must have for any classroom.", author: "Jeff E., Amazon Verified Purchase" },
        { text: "This is an incredible lesson for kids and adults of all ages. The message of kindness and concern for others is clear and beautifully told. The story and illustrations bring joy!", author: "Betty, Amazon Verified Purchase" },
        { text: "The perfect children's book. The beautiful illustrations and lovely story teaches young children love, compassion and empathy. The perfect bedtime story.", author: "Amazon Customer, Verified Purchase" },
        { text: "An excellent story with a great message for children and adults. Her illustrations will delight children and hold their interest.", author: "Ann Dean, Amazon Verified Purchase" },
        { text: "LOVE Norbert Barkah. Susan writes and teaches us a GREAT story, always on TikTok and her writing. We can all learn from Norbert Barkah and Susan. Great for teachers and everyone.", author: "Kathleen Adams, Amazon Verified Purchase" },
        { text: "What an absolutely lovely tale written by Mama Sue to share with the whole family. My daughter loved it, so did I!", author: "Lenny, Amazon Verified Purchase" },
        { text: "Fabulous book, great story and illustrations. I 100% recommend this book. Kids and adults will love Norbert and Mama Sue.", author: "Heidi W., United Kingdom" }
      ];
      var pick = reviews[Math.floor(Math.random() * reviews.length)];
      document.getElementById('quote-text').textContent = '\u201C' + pick.text + '\u201D';
      document.getElementById('quote-author').textContent = pick.author;
    })();
  </script>

  <!-- ====== ENCHANTED FOREST ====== -->
  <section class="section story-world">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <h2 class="fade-in">Step into the Enchanted Forest</h2>
      <p class="fade-in" style="max-width: 680px; margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;">Deeper in the forest, Norbert is joined by Lyra, a tiny fairy whose kind are born without wings. Their wings begin to grow only when they witness true kindness. Lyra awakens when Norbert's bark breaks through the angry growls of a big dog bullying a tiny one. His courage and kindness call her into the world, and from that moment on, she follows him as his witness.</p>
      <div class="world-features">
        <div class="world-feature fade-in">
          <span class="feature-icon">&#127807;</span>
          <h3>Kindness</h3>
          <p>In this forest, kindness is never small. A soft choice, a patient heart, or a gentle word can change the whole path of a story.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="world-feature fade-in">
          <span class="feature-icon">&#10024;</span>
          <h3>Courage</h3>
          <p>Courage here does not shout. It shows up in tender steps, honest feelings, and the quiet strength to keep going when the way feels uncertain.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="world-feature fade-in">
          <span class="feature-icon">&#127774;</span>
          <h3>Inner Light</h3>
          <p>Every story holds a lantern. These tales help readers remember that even in fear, grief, or confusion, there is still light within to guide the next step.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <a href="enchanted-forest.html" class="btn btn--primary" style="margin-top: 3rem;">Enter the Enchanted Forest</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ====== STORYTIME ====== -->
  <section class="section storytime">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-center fade-in">
        <h2>Storytime with Norbert</h2>
        <p style="max-width: 640px; margin: 0 auto 0.5rem;">Storytime with Norbert is a soft place to land. Here, the noise of the world quiets down, imagination takes over, and the stories stay with you long after they end.</p>
        <p style="max-width: 640px; margin: 0 auto 0.5rem;">What makes these storytimes different is that they ask nothing from you. You don't have to do anything here except pause, breathe, and feel safe.</p>
        <p style="max-width: 640px; margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;">Here you'll find story readings, Wednesday Wisdom food for thought, and moments of Norbert living his best life. Stories here may comfort right away. Others make you smile. And a few may linger, because the lesson is wrapped inside the metaphor and opens later.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="max-width: 540px; margin: 2rem auto 0;">
        <div class="fade-in">
          <blockquote class="instagram-media" data-instgrm-permalink="https://www.instagram.com/reel/DC-WhaBMzdj/" data-instgrm-version="14" style="background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 0 auto; max-width:540px; min-width:326px; padding:0; width:99.375%;"></blockquote>
          <script async src="//www.instagram.com/embed.js"></script>
          <p style="text-align: center; margin-top: 1rem; font-style: italic; color: var(--sage-light); font-size: 0.95rem;">The original Tug of War Lesson - the storytime video that inspired the book</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center" style="margin-top: 2rem; display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.75rem; justify-content: center;">
        <a href="https://www.instagram.com/norbertbarkah/" class="btn btn--dark-outline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Watch on Instagram</a>
        <a href="https://www.tiktok.com/@norbertbarkah225" class="btn btn--dark-outline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Watch on TikTok</a>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@NorbertBarkah" class="btn btn--dark-outline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Watch on YouTube</a>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
        <a href="storytime.html" class="btn btn--primary">See More Stories</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ====== ABOUT MAMA SUE ====== -->
  <section class="section about-preview">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="about-grid fade-in">
        <div class="about-portrait">
          <img src="images/mama-sue-headshot.jpg" alt="Susan Higgins, Mama Sue" style="width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover;">
        </div>
        <div class="about-text">
          <h2>About Mama Sue</h2>
          <p class="section-subtitle" style="font-size: 1.4rem;">Storyteller, artist, and the heart behind the enchanted forest</p>
          <p>I'm Susan Higgins, a storyteller, artist, and heart guide who believes in the power of kindness, imagination, and inner light. My stories, shared with Norbert Barkah by my side, are created to help children and grown-ups find courage, connection, and calm in uncertain times. Inspired by the magic of the natural world and the quiet strength of healing, I write to offer a softer place to land.</p>
          <p>What began as reading stories to Norbert grew into something much bigger. People did not just listen, they felt something. From those simple storytime moments came a book, a growing enchanted forest world, and a deeper calling to create stories that comfort, encourage, and help people remember the light within themselves.</p>
          <a href="about.html" class="btn btn--dark-outline" style="margin-top: 1rem;">About Mama Sue</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ====== EMAIL SIGNUP ====== -->
  <section class="section signup" id="signup">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <h2 class="fade-in">Receive gentle notes from the forest</h2>
      <p class="fade-in">Twice a month, I'll send a quiet note from Norbert's world, with story updates, book news, behind-the-scenes glimpses, and sometimes a short story. Think of it as a softer way to stay connected, a little doorway into the enchanted forest.</p>
      <div class="signup-form fade-in">
        <script async data-uid="3c4c1e8b83" src="https://norbert-barkah.kit.com/3c4c1e8b83/index.js"></script>
      </div>
      <p class="signup-note fade-in">No noise, just gentle notes twice a month.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

